In the following project as a first project to apply my python learning i am  build a Blackjack game aka Twenty-One
as previous knowledge in web and oop programming this is a way to start becoming more familiar with Pyhton its libraries
how to integrate and use open sources all the way to building more big projecs AI, automation, web or data related using python

🃏 what blackjack actually is
blackjack is a card game between a player and a dealer.
you are not playing against other players, only against the dealer.
the goal is simple:
👉 get a hand value closer to 21 than the dealer, without going over 21.

🧱 what the game is made of

🎴 deck
standard 52-card deck
sometimes multiple decks are used (but rules stay the same)
card values:
number cards (2–10) → worth their number
face cards (jack, queen, king) → worth 10
ace → can be:
1 or
11 (depends on what helps the hand more)

👥 roles

🧍 player
can make decisions (hit, stand, etc.)

🧑‍💼 dealer
follows fixed rules (no decision-making freedom like player)

▶️ how a round starts
player places a bet
both player and dealer get 2 cards each
player: both cards face up

dealer:
1 card face up (visible)
1 card face down (hidden)

🧮 hand value calculation
you add up card values.
special rule for ace:
if counting it as 11 makes you go over 21 → it becomes 1 instead
👉 example:
ace + 9 = 20
ace + 9 + 5 = 15 (ace becomes 1, not 11)

🎯 blackjack (natural)
if your first 2 cards = 21 exactly:
(ace + 10-value card)
this is called blackjack
usually beats everything except dealer blackjack

🔁 player turn (your decisions)
you go first.
you can choose:
1. hit
take another card
can repeat as many times as you want

2. stand
stop taking cards
keep your current total

3. bust
if your total > 21
👉 you immediately lose

🤖 dealer turn (fixed behavior)
after player finishes:
dealer reveals hidden card, then:
must hit if total < 17
must stand if total ≥ 17
👉 important detail:
some rules say dealer must hit on "soft 17" (ace counted as 11)
others say stand — depends on version

🏁 how the winner is decided
after both turns:

cases:
✅ player wins if:
player total > dealer total (≤ 21)
dealer busts (> 21)

❌ player loses if:
player busts
dealer total > player total

🤝 push (tie)
same total → bet returned

💰 payouts (basic)
normal win → 1:1 (you double your bet)
blackjack → usually 3:2
loss → you lose your bet

🧠 important concepts
🔹 hard hand
no ace OR ace counted as 1
🔹 soft hand
ace counted as 11
example:
ace + 6 = soft 17
🔹 bust logic
a hand is bust if:
total > 21 after adjusting aces if possible
🔹 multiple hits
you can keep hitting until:
you stand
or you bust

⚠️ optional rules (depending on version)
these exist in real blackjack but you may or may not include them:
🔸 double down
double your bet
take exactly 1 more card
then forced to stand
🔸 split
if first 2 cards have same value:
split into 2 hands
play each separately
🔸 insurance
if dealer shows ace:
side bet in case dealer has blackjack

🔄 full round summary
bet placed
cards dealt (2 each)
check for blackjack
player turn (hit/stand until done)
dealer turn (automatic rules)
compare results
payout

🧩 edge cases you must understand
ace switching between 1 and 11 dynamically
blackjack only counts on first 2 cards
dealer plays after player finishes
player bust = instant loss (dealer doesn’t even need to play)
dealer bust = all remaining players win

🧠 mental model (important)
think of blackjack as:
a state-based game
with:
a hand total
card list
a turn phase (player / dealer)
rules that trigger automatically